The Future of Collaboration Apps

Antonio Lain, Caf.js Labs

antlai@cafjs.com

1. Vendor Independence

  • Change video API provider,
    • maintain the experience

2. Best of Breed

  • Pick your "whiteboard" app
    • from an independent store
  • Pay-per-use
  • Fully managed service
  • Customize app with
    • branding + APIs

3. Share Local Devices

  • Touch and smell
  • Telemedicine
  • Fitness
  • Smart lights
  • Toys (adult & kids)
  • Education
  • Car diagnostics
  • Real estate
  • Industrial sensors
  • Digital Twins
  • Many others...

4. Make a Global Party

  • Synchronize millions of actions
    • across the globe,
    • accurately (most <100 msec jitter),
    • using global time (UTC),
    • or the video stream

5. Make it Personal

  • Each stream is different
    • Language
    • Local context
    • Preferences
    • Collective input
    • Ads

6. Mobile First

  • ONE window
  • Responsive design
  • Pixel-perfect, smooth animations
  • Hardware constraints
    • Media codecs
    • GPU rendering
  • Bandwidth adaptation

7. Transition to VR/AR

  • Pick best UI for the device
    • Responsive design on steroids
  • Seamless integration
    • with legacy devices in 2D

Summary

  • Vendor independence
  • Best-of-breed
  • Share local devices
  • Coordinate global actions in real-time
  • Personalize streams
  • Mobile-first design
  • Bridge to VR/AR

Caf.js Labs

  • Building a platform to create, host, and monetize
    • a new generation of collaboration apps,
    • using the WAB (Web App Background) architecture,
    • and implemented with the Caf.js framework + Caf.js Cloud

WAB (Web App Background) Architecture

  • Merge independent layers at the destination
